"n. 赞美之词(extravagant praise)；狂想曲 【英】 n. 溢美之词 (extravagant praise) 【记】 rhapso(缝)+ody(颂歌 )→把颂歌连接起来→ 赞美 【例】 She went into rhapsodies over the beauty of the scene. (她赞美风景之美) n. 溢美之词; 狂想曲(在讲演或写作中过分地热情的感情表达) 【记】r, hap(n 运气), sody: 有运气－赞美rhapso缝, ody = ode(n 颂歌)一把颂歌缝起来一赞美 【记】rap 说，说唱歌曲 + ode 歌，颂诗 【相关】ode 颂诗, 赋，episode 插曲，melody 悦耳的音调，monody 独唱, parody 模仿滑稽作品，prosody 做诗法，韵律学，rhapsody 狂想曲，荷马史诗，threnode 挽歌 rhapsody (n.)  1540s, ""epic poem,"" from Middle French rhapsodie, from Latin rhapsodia, from Greek rhapsoidia ""verse composition, recitation of epic poetry; a book, a lay, a canto,"" from rhapsodos ""reciter of epic poems,"" literally ""one who stitches or strings songs together,"" from rhaptein ""to stitch, sew, weave"" (see wrap (v.)) + oide ""song"" (see ode). Meaning ""exalted enthusiastic feeling or expression"" is from 1630s. Meaning ""sprightly musical composition"" is first recorded 1850s."
